|GKB-- Druid Companions ------------------------------------------|000

Druids can keep a living menagerie.  Each companion unlocks at a
different guild level, can be summoned beside the others, and grows
stronger as it fights with you.

|CKBcompanions|000
  Show every companion, its role, current, nwyfre cost, level, XP to
  next level, and status.

|CKBcompanions summon <animal>|000
  Call one unlocked companion.  The call consumes that companion's
  required nwyfre current and profession materials, then completes
  after a short preparation timer.  Moving or entering combat breaks
  the pattern.

|CKBcompanions dismiss <animal>|000
  Release one active companion back to the wild.

|CKBcompanions dismiss all|000
  Release the whole menagerie.

|CKBcompanions name <animal> <name>|000
|CKBcompanions rename <animal> <name>|000
  Give one unlocked companion a personal name.  Names must be 3 to
  11 letters, and can be used in companion commands.

|CKBcompanions unname <animal>|000
  Clear a companion's personal name.

Unlocked companions:

  |CKBJaguar   |000 guild  5   stalker
  |CKBWolf     |000 guild  9   hunter
  |CKBBoar     |000 guild 13   breaker
  |CKBStag     |000 guild 17   warden
  |CKBBear     |000 guild 21   guardian
  |CKBLion     |000 guild 25   apex

Companions gain experience from battle participation and auto-level
from their saved XP.  A companion that dies is wounded, not erased.
It keeps its XP and level, but must recover before it can answer
your call again.

Each companion answers a different current and material pattern.
Use |CKBcompanions|000 to see your adjusted nwyfre costs and exact
profession material requirements.
